{"name": "pyxmv", "metadata": {"name": "pyxmv", "version": "0.6.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12"], "home_page": "https://github.com/lou1306/pyxmv", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pexpect", "typer-slim", "msgspec"], "summary": "(Unofficial) Python interface to nuXmv", "upload_time": 1734809754}, "documentation": ["# `pyxmv` - (Unofficial) Python interface to nuXmv\n\n[nuXmv](https://nuxmv.fbk.eu/) is a state-of-the-art symbolic model checker for\nthe analysis of finite- and infinite- state systems.\n\n`pyxmv` is a (very much WIP) wrapper for the nuXmv command-line interface; it\naims at providing APIs for several features, and comes with a small CLI to\nshowcase what it can do.\n\nThe CLI itself should, in time, become an alternative to the official one with\na focus on automation/scriptability/interop with other\ntools/pipelines/workflows.\n\n# Quickstart\n\nBesides nuXmv, the tool requires Python >= 3.10 and Poetry.\n\nAfter cloning this repository:\n\n```bash\ncd pyxmv\npoetry update\npoetry install\npyxmv --help\n```\n\n## Install options\n\n```bash\npoetry install --only main  # Only installs packages that pyxmv needs to run\npoetry install              # Also install dev dependencies\npoetry install --all-extras # Installs all optional packages\n```\n\nDev dependencies are packages that are only required for contributing or\ntesting, such as [`mypy`](https://www.mypy-lang.org/). Since v0.3.0 we strive\nto have a codebase that can pass _at least_ `mypy --allow-redefinition`,\n_at least_ on commits tagged with a version number.\n\nAt the moment the only optional package is\n[`rich`](https://github.com/Textualize/rich).\nWhen installed, it provides somewhat fancier output, especially on `--help`.\n\n# Future work\n\n* Support alternative simulation heuristics\n\n* Support NuSMV\n\n# Licensing caveats\n\n`pyxmv` is MIT-licensed, but it is perfectly useless unless you obtain a copy\nof nuXmv. Licensing restrictions forbid me from redistributing it, but it may\nbe downloaded [here](https://nuxmv.fbk.eu/download.html)\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pyxmv.app", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pyxmv.app.callback", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "debug", "type": {"name": "cli.Debug", "xref": {"fqname": "pyxmv.app..cli.Debug", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["(Unofficial) Python API and CLI for NuXmv."]}, {"name": "pyxmv.app.version", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Print version information and exit."]}, {"name": "pyxmv.app.dump", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": {"name": "Trace | Outcome", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "fmt", "type": {"name": "cli.OutputFormat", "xref": {"fqname": "pyxmv.app..cli.OutputFormat", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxmv.app.dump_states", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "states", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fmt", "type": {"name": "cli.OutputFormat", "xref": {"fqname": "pyxmv.app..cli.OutputFormat", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "err_code", "type": {"name": "cli.ExitCode", "xref": {"fqname": "pyxmv.app..cli.ExitCode", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pyxmv.app.simulate", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fname", "type": {"name": "cli.Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pyxmv.app..cli.Path", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"n